@page "/terms"
@layout PublicLayout

<div class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-nav">
        <a href="/" class="legal-nav-brand">
            <img src="images/logo.png" alt="Plantitask" class="legal-nav-logo" />
            <span class="text-sora">PLANTITASK</span>
        </a>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-content">
        <h1 class="text-sora legal-title">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM d, yyyy")</p>

        <p>
            Welcome to Plantitask. By creating an account or using our platform, you
            agree to these Terms of Service. Please read them carefully.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">1. About Plantitask</h2>
        <p>Plantitask is a nature-themed, gamified task management platform built for small teams. We provide tools for organizing work through Kanban boards, real-time collaboration, group management, and progress tracking. Completing tasks contributes to a visual tree-growing experience within the platform.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">2. Your Account</h2>
        <p>You must provide accurate information when creating an account. You are responsible for maintaining the security of your password and account. You must be at least 16 years old to use Plantitask. One person may not maintain more than one account. You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your account.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">3. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to use Plantitask to upload content that is illegal, harmful, or violates the rights of others, attempt to gain unauthorized access to other accounts or systems, interfere with or disrupt the platform or its infrastructure, use automated tools to scrape or extract data from the platform, or impersonate another person or entity. We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">4. Your Content</h2>
        <p>You retain ownership of all content you create on Plantitask, including tasks, comments, and file attachments. By using the platform, you grant us a limited license to store, display, and transmit your content as necessary to provide the service. We do not claim intellectual property rights over your content. When you delete content, it is soft-deleted (hidden from view but retained in a deactivated state for up to 90 days) before being permanently removed. See our Privacy Policy for details on data retention.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">5. Groups and Collaboration</h2>
        <p>When you create or join a group, other members of that group can view and interact with tasks, comments, and attachments within that group. Group owners and managers can manage membership and roles. If you leave a group, your previously created content within that group remains accessible to other group members. Removing a group member does not automatically delete their contributions.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">6. Free Tier and Paid Plans</h2>
        <p>Plantitask offers a free tier with core functionality for small teams. We may introduce paid plans in the future for teams that exceed the free member limit or for access to cosmetic features such as custom trees, rare saplings, seasonal items, and team themes. No core task management features will ever be placed behind a paywall. Pricing and plan details will be communicated clearly before any charges apply. We will provide reasonable notice before any changes to pricing that affect existing users.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">7. Our Mission and Revenue</h2>
        <p>Plantitask is built with a mission. After covering operational costs including hosting, infrastructure, and platform maintenance, we donate a portion of remaining revenue to verified tree-planting foundations worldwide, including organizations such as One Tree Planted and Trees for the Future. This commitment is a core part of our identity, not a promotional campaign. We will maintain transparency about our donations and may display aggregate donation figures on our platform.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">8. Availability and Changes</h2>
        <p>We strive to keep Plantitask available and reliable, but we do not guarantee uninterrupted access. We may modify, suspend, or discontinue features with reasonable notice. We will make best efforts to notify users of significant changes in advance. Scheduled maintenance will be communicated when possible.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>Plantitask is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the platform. Our total liability for any claim related to the service is limited to the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim, or 50 EUR, whichever is greater.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">10. Termination</h2>
        <p>You may delete your account at any time through your profile settings. We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these terms. Upon termination, your data will be handled according to our Privacy Policy, including the soft-deletion retention period.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the European Union and the applicable national laws of the country in which Plantitask operates. Any disputes will be resolved in the competent courts of that jurisdiction.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms of Service from time to time. We will notify registered users of significant changes via email at least 30 days before they take effect. Your continued use of the platform after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</p>

        <h2 class="text-sora">13. Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about these Terms of Service, contact us at legal@plantitask.com.</p>
    </div>
</div>